The '''Party of United Pensioners''' ({{lang-sr|Партија уједињених пензионера}}, ''Partija ujedinjenih penzionera'', PUP) is a [[Centrism|centrist]] political party representing the [[List of pensioners' parties|interests of pensioners]] in [[Republika Srpska]].

==History==
The PUP contested the [[Republika Srpska general election, 2010|2010 elections]] in Republika Srpska in an alliance with the [[Socialist Party (Bosnia and Herzegovina)|Socialist Party]], winning four seats.<ref>[http://izbori.ba/Finalni2010/Finalni/NarodnaSkupstinaRS/ZbirniRezultate.aspx  Republika Srpska National Assembly] Central Elections Commission</ref>

The [[Republika Srpska general election, 2014|2014 elections]] saw the party join an alliance with the [[Serb Democratic Party (Bosnia and Herzegovina)|Serb Democratic Party]] and the [[Serbian Radical Party of the Republika Srpska|Serbian Radical Party]]. The alliance emerged as the second largest faction in the [[National Assembly (Republika Srpska)|National Assembly]], winning 24 of the 83 seats.<ref>[http://www.izbori.ba/Utvrdjeni2014/Finalni/NarodnaSkupstinaRS/ZbirniRezultate.aspx Republika Srpska National Assembly] Central Elections Commission</ref>

